Package stincmale.ratmex.executor

Class Rate

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.ratmex.executor.Rate

  • @Immutable
public final class Rate
extends java.lang.Object
    A representation of a rate. Formally represents a set of probability distributions which have probability density functions equal to 0 for any rate values outside [minValue; maxValue].

      • compareTo

        public final int compareTo​(double value,
                           java.time.Duration unit)
        Decides if the provided rate (represented by value and unit) lies within, on the left of or on the right of the [minValue, maxValue] interval (accounting that the interval may be expressed in different units).
        Parameters:
        value - A value of the rate.
        unit - A time interval in which value is measured, i.e. rate is measured in unit-1.
        Returns:
        • 0 if the provided rate lies within the interval expressed by this Rate;
        • 1 if the provided rate lies on the left of the interval expressed by this Rate;
        • -1 if the provided rate lies on the left of the interval expressed by this Rate.
        So in a way these values are consistent with the logic of Comparable.compareTo(Object).

      • compareTo
